		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Samael Aun Weor</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:182px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Saw1.gif" class="image" title="Samael Aun Weor."><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/3/33/Saw1.gif" width="180" height="265" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Saw1.gif" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
Samael Aun Weor.</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><b>Samael Aun Weor</b> (born <b>Víctor Manuel Gómez Rodríguez</b>) (March 6, 1917 - December 24, 1977) was a spiritual teacher, <a href="/wiki/Occult" title="Occult">occultist</a>, <a href="/wiki/Esotericism" title="Esotericism">esotericist</a> and author. He established himself in <a href="/wiki/Mexico" title="Mexico">Mexico</a> in the 1950s where he founded the 'International Gnostic Movement'. <sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup>In his over sixty books and hundreds of held conferences, he describes a teaching called "<a href="/wiki/Gnosis" title="Gnosis">Gnosis</a>", the Greek word for "knowledge", from which is derived the name "<a href="/wiki/Gnosticism" title="Gnosticism">Gnosticism</a>", designating a sectarian <a href="/wiki/Syncretism" title="Syncretism">syncretism</a> which appeared at the beginning of the Christian Era and was considered <a href="/wiki/Heresy" title="Heresy">heresy</a> by the <a href="/wiki/Church_Fathers" title="Church Fathers">Church Fathers</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1" title=""><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
